refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 public static arrayUnitEnum::cases




 This method will return a packed array of all cases in an enumeration, in order of declaration.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Basic usage


    The following example illustrates how enum cases are returned.



<?php
enum Suit
{
    case Hearts;
    case Diamonds;
    case Clubs;
    case Spades;
}

var_dump(Suit::cases());
?>


   &example.outputs;


array(4) {
    [0]=>
    enum(Suit::Hearts)
    [1]=>
    enum(Suit::Diamonds)
    [2]=>
    enum(Suit::Clubs)
    [3]=>
    enum(Suit::Spades)
}
